main event: Five members of the Thunderbird acro team observed a round cylindrical object in flight for 35 minutes.
interesting points: The object was larger than a basketball and had clean white edges,The object was stationary in the sky,The sighting lasted more than a minute and a half,The location of the sighting was southwest of Winston Salem, North Carolina,There is a reference to Venus in the comments of the report.
witness description: members of the Thunderbird acro team
